lead_paragraph: Ramon Sessions scored 18 points and had a season-high 13 assists while starting in place of the injured John Wall to help the Washington Wizards defeat the Brooklyn Nets 121-103 on Wednesday night.

headline.print_headline: With Wall Out, Sessions Steps Up, Wizards Beat Nets 121-103
